# Can you discuss a time when you had to overcome a significant challenge in your previous job?
One significant challenge I faced as a Backend Engineer at MimosaTEK was developing a statistics module for an IoT Tree Management platform. I was responsibile for building GraphqlAPIs that aggregated tree scan data to track workers' daily activities and progress. The system used MongoDB, and at that time I had limited experience with MongoDB aggregation pipelines, but the project required complex data processing and accurate reporting.
To overcome this, I studied MongoDB's aggregation framework through official documentaion and hands-on experimentation, breaking down complex queries into smaller stages and iterating to improve performance and correctness. I also used AI tools to accelerate my learning.
As a result, I successfully delivered APIs that provided clear, meaningful insights into worker productivity, helping managers monitor farm operations more effectively. The experience strenghthened my ability to quickly learn new technologies and design efficient data-processing solutions in a real-work productoin environment.

# How do you prioritize your tasks when you have multiple deadlines?
When dealing with a variety of deadlines, I sort out my tasks based on a scoring system of urgency and importance. I also utilize specialized tools to facillitate management process.

For example, in my previous position as a FullStack Engineer at MimosaTEK, I not only took part in the development of new features for a user-facing application but only was in charge of maintaining existing internal products. I determined that focusing on releasing new features promptly had a higher impact on user satisfaction and kept them involved in the business. By addressing those issues first, we are able to keep users' engagement and brought money into the company.

After identifying what was urgent, I broke down complex tasks into smaller ones and employed Larksuite to organize them by their deadlines and impact. This approach allowed me to allocate specific time blocks dedicated to feature development while also ensuring that I wasn't neglecting critical maintainance probles. Following this method consistently also prevented me from feeling burn out at the mid term.

Overall, my primary strategy revolves around accessing priority based on urgency and importance. This ensures that I and my team members are on the same page and the deadlines are met consistently.


